Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.43,0:00:18.40,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.44,0:01:58.38,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 15 - Two Homes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.29,0:02:18.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, it's raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.78,0:02:24.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's raining, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:25.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Started so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:26.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're out of luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.10,0:02:35.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sticky and her babies\Nwill get wet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.30,0:02:57.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, ain't no helping it.\NWhy don't we rest a spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.81,0:03:06.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come get inside here.\NYou're sodden wet, ain't ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.58,0:03:08.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Only together with the goat, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.96,0:03:09.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The goat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.70,0:03:19.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probly just a rain shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.39,0:03:20.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:22.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Work goin' smoothly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:25.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The wood is harder than I thought,\Nso it'll take a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:29.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As much I woulda liked to help,\NI ain't cut out for doin' carpenter's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.69,0:03:31.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:34.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We were never counting on you\Nto prop us here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:39.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,'Sides, if a bungler such as myself woulda helped you,\Nwe'd only arrive to a house that goes "wobble-wobble"!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.11,0:03:43.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Eh? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.97,0:03:51.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! The goat - alright, can't be helped.\NBut you two must definitely go hide in the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.90,0:03:53.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:55.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we're already in here, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.78,0:03:57.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're being mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.14,0:03:59.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But there's no reason\Nfor you two to be in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.86,0:04:01.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You were on your way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.51,0:04:04.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're just as fine here.\NRight, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.85,0:04:05.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.85,0:04:07.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:10.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a fuss over nothing, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.08,0:04:13.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's Ben who's saying we should go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.50,0:04:16.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're not someone to tell us do that, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.62,0:04:19.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This tent belongs to me and Dr. Deighton.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.51,0:04:21.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it was {\i1}our{\i0} sleeping place before you came!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.95,0:04:23.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.39,0:04:24.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.53,0:04:27.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But now you have\Nthe house over there for yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.07,0:04:30.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can't stand that godforsaken house!\NIt's all cramped and dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.60,0:04:31.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.20,0:04:33.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.11,0:04:33.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.90,0:04:35.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be saying such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:41.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You know both dad and mom\Ndon't consider that house marvelous either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.24,0:04:43.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even Clara is just bearing with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.62,0:04:47.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know what dad and me\Nare currently working for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.45,0:04:51.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We know that, alright. You're working\Non making this house bigger, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.27,0:04:53.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But there's no way of knowing\Njust how long will it take.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.83,0:04:55.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it'll take that long, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.66,0:04:58.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that I'm not a carpenter by trade,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.04,0:05:00.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,and Ben cannot yet stand on his own either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.79,0:05:04.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we keep doing everything in our power\Nto make this house
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.45,0:05:07.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,much bigger and comfortable for living\Nas soon as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.38,0:05:11.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm asking you both, Kate and Lucy-May,\Nfor a bit more of patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.96,0:05:12.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.90,0:05:13.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.37,0:05:15.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:23.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! Mother, another leak over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:29.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... It seems this roof is thoroughly tattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.61,0:05:37.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tob! Don't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.21,0:05:42.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Comment: 0,0:05:42.18,0:05:44.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.69,0:05:48.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your father and the others\Nprobably chose the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.21,0:05:49.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.59,0:05:52.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd really love to start living\Nin a proper house soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.18,0:05:55.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad may not have admitted it,\Nbut that was probably one big mistake, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:56.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:05:59.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Selling away our prefabricated home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:00.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.14,0:06:05.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad said he had to sell it\Nbecause he couldn't move it to Adelaide anyhow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.77,0:06:09.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Pettywell was apparently able\Nto move it no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.11,0:06:11.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well that was because Mr. Pettywell is so wealthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.49,0:06:14.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, that was an obvious miscalculation\Non dad's part.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:15.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.01,0:06:20.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know. It's no use lamenting something\Nthat's already done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.81,0:06:25.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your father promised to make it\Ninto a way less objectionable place very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.60,0:06:27.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's really getting on my nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:28.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.61,0:06:31.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At Mr. Pettywell's plot,\Nthey've finished the foundation already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:33.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.39,0:06:37.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And it's no wonder.\NThat's what prefabricated homes are for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.50,0:06:43.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.02,0:06:44.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.05,0:06:47.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The rain is too strong.\NWe should give everyone a rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.50,0:06:48.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess we've no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.82,0:06:50.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll go tell them to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.40,0:06:52.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Everyone!\NLet's take a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.29,0:06:57.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Once a professional carpenter joins the team,\Nthe rate of their advance becomes a whole other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.70,0:06:59.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:08.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem to be stopping at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.59,0:07:11.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, have you been to the Macs today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.38,0:07:14.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, I was just thinking of going there,\Nwhen suddenly, this rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.98,0:07:16.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That sir next door is still unwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.76,0:07:19.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he ain't too well, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:23.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I felt relieved by his fever finally subsiding,\Nit went right back up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.40,0:07:30.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, we've prepared some tea.\NDoctor is welcome, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.65,0:07:33.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, much obliged.\NWell, if you don't mind me going ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:35.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about us, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.30,0:07:38.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The children will have to stay here until later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.88,0:07:39.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's unfair!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.99,0:07:42.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The roof is leaking terribly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:46.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you two come inside, you'll end up soaked\Nas there's nowhere to hide from the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.00,0:07:52.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I sure hope it stops raining soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.91,0:07:59.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.73,0:08:02.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, another leak formed there as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.78,0:08:05.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, sorry to trouble,\Nbut if you could move just a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.38,0:08:06.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:10.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple, if I were you,\NI'd also try to repair this house as soon as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.99,0:08:14.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If it's that bad, Annie,\Nshouldn't I ask for someone else's help?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.53,0:08:17.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And where will you find anyone willing to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.49,0:08:20.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. If only Mr. Jamling was here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:22.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But he's still on the beach, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.50,0:08:24.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, his leg should have healed by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:26.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.38,0:08:29.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... How long ago was it, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.10,0:08:32.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, gotta be able to walk by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:35.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then he might've left for Adelaide as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:38.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If he comes through here,\NI wonder if he'll stop by to say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.76,0:08:40.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You told him how to find us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.39,0:08:45.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. Ah, I suppose he's still stuck\Nin the seaside camp, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.69,0:08:51.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even supposing his leg had healed, I doubt he could\Nfind a cart to carry his things at a moment's notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.33,0:08:56.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If only we could ask for Mr. Jamling's help, I'm sure,\Nrepairing this house wouldn't take nearly as long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.37,0:09:05.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Isn't it supposed to be over by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.62,0:09:11.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Back to work! To work!\NThe rain had nearly stopped already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.78,0:09:12.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.07,0:09:16.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What does he mean?\NIt's still raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:20.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Mr. Jamling?\NIf it's fine with you, we can renew the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:23.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This rain is nothing special at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.13,0:09:26.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"Because he's paying us\Nmore than double the usual wage", isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.50,0:09:30.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it may have played its part.\NLook, here he comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.27,0:09:36.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, Mr. Jamling, I hope to see the favor\Nof letting you have a rain break returned now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.59,0:09:38.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But the rain hasn't stopped yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:43.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, is that so? And to me it seems\Nlike there's barely any precipitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.88,0:09:48.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, alright, we get it.\NWe'll work one more shift until the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.80,0:09:50.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.01,0:09:56.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, put off dillydallying\Nand do your best for some more!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.47,0:10:00.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's try our best, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:03.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll only be able\Nto saw a few until the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.39,0:10:05.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll saw what we can saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.10,0:10:27.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.58,0:10:30.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Away! Away!\NYou can't go around eating my stock-in-trade!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:34.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, the rain is finally over.\NGo out an chew some grass now. Grass!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.59,0:10:43.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, my. I sure wouldn't want\Nto spend a night in one tent with you three.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.89,0:10:58.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Deighton is visiting our neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:11:00.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go and check them out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.49,0:11:01.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.30,0:11:04.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Cause we need to know our neighbors well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.15,0:11:06.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whaddya mean by "know well"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.20,0:11:09.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Means seeing what their rooms are like inside,\Nwhat's in them and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.99,0:11:12.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go peek inside through the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.56,0:11:15.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, do you quite realize\Njust what are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.80,0:11:19.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that's just cause I'm so curious about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.27,0:11:21.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know what you can do\Nand what you can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.42,0:11:23.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I do know, for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.21,0:11:27.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to agree that we haven't seen\NMrs. Mac's husband not even once yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:30.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, good day to you, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:32.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well that's cause he's ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.73,0:11:35.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's only natural we can't see him\Nas he has to sleep inside all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:38.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I want to know -\Nwhat does he look like and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.89,0:11:39.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:42.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.07,0:11:44.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really mean to say\Nyou don't wanna find out at all ?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.96,0:11:48.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I... Well, of course, I do wanna know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:51.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.56,0:12:09.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's use this window to peek inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.40,0:12:11.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.99,0:12:13.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's a no-go, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.84,0:12:14.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.98,0:12:17.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You know exactly what!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:20.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I came to realize\Nthat peeking into other's homes is very rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.79,0:12:25.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning you won't do it with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.81,0:12:30.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, fair! It's an ugly business -\Nthat much I could tell myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.79,0:12:35.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But also... I can't help wondering\Nwhat Mrs. Mac's husband is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.28,0:12:59.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't startle me like that, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:00.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, you seen it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.34,0:13:01.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seen what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.35,0:13:05.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean "What"? You wanted to see\Nthe house inside, didn't you? What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.32,0:13:09.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here is their living room.\NMrs. Mac and Doctor went into another room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.19,0:13:13.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, that must be where they have\Nthe sick room, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.71,0:13:14.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.71,0:13:18.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, was that door closer\Nto that side of the house or to this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.19,0:13:19.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:21.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Which one do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.08,0:13:25.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll know at once when you see it.\NJust take a look yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.01,0:13:27.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way! I can't look in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.59,0:13:29.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're acting kinda kooky, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.59,0:13:31.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, just tell me which one it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.16,0:13:33.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's right there, the door in the back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.10,0:13:34.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so it's the one in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:37.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the window to the sick room\Nis on the other side of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:43.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up after me, Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.77,0:13:51.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, must be this window.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.48,0:13:56.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You do the peeking this time, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.83,0:14:00.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Surely enough, that must be you!\NDidn't I tell you I won't look?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:04.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, just take a peek through this window.\NI'm sure you'll see everything well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.19,0:14:07.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is just getting ridiculous now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.60,0:14:15.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:17.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, how is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.39,0:14:20.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How's what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.89,0:14:23.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What you're looking at, of course!\NJust tell me already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.78,0:14:25.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see the patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:29.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, you see him or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:32.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Tell me now, you meanie!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.32,0:14:33.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:34.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:38.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This here looks like Mr. Bernard's bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.05,0:14:39.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.10,0:14:41.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The patient is in another room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.79,0:14:44.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But hey, what's Mr. Bernard's bedroom like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:46.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just peek in yourself, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:47.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hush!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:50.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, another window\Nfor the sick room, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.96,0:14:52.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After me, Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.19,0:14:55.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not doing any more peeking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.28,0:15:02.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not very logical of you to say that.\NYou've done peeking two times already.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.54,0:15:03.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And so I refuse now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.08,0:15:07.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, look: you already misbehaved twice anyhow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.77,0:15:11.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So just adding one more to the stack\Nwon't make any difference, don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.40,0:15:13.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna do any more peeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.21,0:15:15.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that window is way too high\Nfor my stature anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.90,0:15:21.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, it's too far even for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.31,0:15:24.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if we find some platform to climb on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.51,0:15:25.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.79,0:15:35.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.04,0:15:36.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"No" means "No"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.50,0:15:37.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're a selfish one...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.52,0:15:39.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you go ahead and peek in?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.30,0:15:45.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Let's peek in together, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.46,0:15:46.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Together?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:51.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. By doing something together,\Nwe can halve the guilt for misbehaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.40,0:15:52.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.72,0:15:54.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now get on and let's peek in together, deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.40,0:16:09.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, Kate, Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.94,0:16:12.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:16.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You brute, brute, brute!\NOh, this Billy is unbearable!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.65,0:16:21.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Ouch! Ouch, ouch, ouch! It hurts, aye!\NHey, what's the matter with you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:23.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least tell me what's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.33,0:16:28.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy, you've finally made it to Adelaide, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.32,0:16:31.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We arrived here two days ago in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.30,0:16:34.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our house is a bit difficult to see from here,\Nbut it's really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.92,0:16:38.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Thank goodness we're\Nin the same neighborhood. Right, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.27,0:16:41.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But don't slap people on the butt\Nlike you just did, Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.23,0:16:46.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My bad, alright. But I also wasn't expecting you two\Nto be so startled by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.40,0:16:48.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was real rude on my part though, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.38,0:16:50.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine already, you're forgiven.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.48,0:16:51.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.47,0:16:54.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, though, I'm kinda jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.15,0:16:54.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.86,0:16:58.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In this place, that's one impressive house you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.07,0:17:00.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mine is still nothing more than a tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.69,0:17:03.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, that one is Mrs. Mac's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.24,0:17:04.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Mac?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.55,0:17:09.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. As for our house, look -\Nthe pitiful cabin over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:14.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.43,0:17:17.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means you two were peeking\Ninto other people's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.31,0:17:19.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You could say so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.90,0:17:24.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we still had a pretty solid reason to do that.\NThat being Dr. Deighton...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.13,0:17:27.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You got Dr. Deighton here with you?\NIn this neighborhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:31.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. He lives in a tent by our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:33.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? So that's how it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.38,0:17:38.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Dr. Deighton, my dad's leg\Ngot much better and in no time at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.67,0:17:40.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He even returned to work already.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.39,0:17:42.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mighty glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.30,0:17:45.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He owes your daddy and Ben a big one\Nfor saving his skin in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.47,0:17:49.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad even said he won't ever forget\Nthe kindness of those two in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.27,0:17:51.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our dad merely did what\Nanyone else would've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.16,0:17:55.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, actually... Dad probably hasn't a clue!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.94,0:18:00.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,While working so close, he never even stopped\Nby your place to say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.05,0:18:01.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And where is he working?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.19,0:18:08.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right there, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:13.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Over there, meaning at Mr. Pettywell's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.45,0:18:17.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. He's working for that moneybag Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.59,0:18:23.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell's messenger came all the way\Nto the beach camp, bowing and begging my dad to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.28,0:18:24.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.36,0:18:27.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They even took care of an oxcart\Nto bring along our stuff.
Comment: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:29.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.39,0:18:42.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true Mr. Jamling\Nis now working on Mr. Pettywell's site?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.74,0:18:45.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've seen it ourselves, very closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.07,0:18:46.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.49,0:18:50.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Mr. Jamling was assembling\Nthe prefabricated house there, that's for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.51,0:18:52.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.71,0:18:59.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ben. In case you're directing those words\Nat Mr. Jamling, you're making a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.20,0:19:01.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.68,0:19:05.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jamling is free to work at anyone's site,\Nthat is his basic right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.98,0:19:08.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it happens to be Mr. Pettywell's site!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.72,0:19:15.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back when we saved Mr. Jamling in the woods,\Nhe was crying with gratitude, mind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.39,0:19:19.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Ben, you're forgetting\Nthe most important thing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.18,0:19:20.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.40,0:19:24.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It may stand true that Mr. Pettywell\Nis infinitely intolerable,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.00,0:19:26.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but that doesn't make him\Nour sworn enemy or adversary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.49,0:19:30.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back when Clara was in agony\Ndue to her deteriorating condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.83,0:19:33.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,he broke the line and proceeded to disembark first!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.54,0:19:35.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then the fresh meat we got from Mr. Parker
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.87,0:19:38.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,got snatched away by Mr. Pettywell's dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.70,0:19:42.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, my. You're still hung up\Neven on such petty things?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.69,0:19:47.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then there was also the oxcart intended for us,\Nbut Mr. Pettywell managed to take that away as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.42,0:19:51.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember how we had to walk our feet off\Nto find a replacement oxcart?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.39,0:19:53.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.89,0:19:56.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because the transportation here is such a bust,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.24,0:19:59.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,we figured transporting\Nour prefabricated home is a non-starter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:02.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you made a decision to sell it.\NDidn't you, dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.78,0:20:06.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think... I think that was indeed\Na mistake on my part.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.78,0:20:11.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why Mr. Pettywell\Nwas the last person you'd want to sell it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.28,0:20:14.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But as cruel irony would have it,\Nthat house landed right into Mr. Pettywell's hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.99,0:20:16.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That was a pure coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.91,0:20:21.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, all the Jamlings\Nwere perfectly aware of how it actually is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.01,0:20:23.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben! That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.29,0:20:26.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Mr. Jamling will work wherever he pleases.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.28,0:20:28.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can stop Mr. Jamling from that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.83,0:20:34.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come now, Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.69,0:20:53.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:58.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good! Nail that down real tight, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.60,0:21:03.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Next, we're setting up that pillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.31,0:21:05.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.42,0:21:06.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.63,0:21:09.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?\NI noticed you've been watching us for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.70,0:21:13.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was hanging out with Mr. Popple's daughters\NKate and Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:14.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.08,0:21:18.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right! Right there.\NNow nail it hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.56,0:21:22.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This house is the house Mr. Popple\Nbrought along from England, innit?
Comment: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:24.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.77,0:21:27.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? Uh, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.36,0:21:31.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But listen here boy,\Nthis house now belongs to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.23,0:21:34.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, if you look over there,\Nit's Mr. Popple's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.78,0:21:35.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:37.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You already knew, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.61,0:21:41.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd think Mr. Popple would buy a house\Nright across the street from my plot, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.73,0:21:46.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, Mr. Popple\Nis planning to rebuild this seedy shack.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.19,0:21:53.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, actually. Dad, Dr. Deighton\Nalso ended up staying at Mr. Popple's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.28,0:22:22.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous to keep working when it's so dark.\NLet's continue tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.80,0:22:23.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.79,0:22:28.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you tired, Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.30,0:22:29.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.51,0:22:31.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotten quite used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.26,0:22:33.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.49,0:22:37.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's coming here, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.44,0:22:43.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mr. Jamling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.36,0:22:45.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jamling!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.21,0:22:59.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Mr. Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.29,0:23:03.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Good evening to you, Mr. Jamling.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.59,0:23:08.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is your leg doing better now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.90,0:23:12.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Through your care,\Nit's just as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.97,0:23:14.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.47,0:23:16.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.31,0:23:17.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.88,0:23:21.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there something I could help you with?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.18,0:23:27.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I know how it sounds from my own lips,\Nbut I'm actually a master carpenter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.80,0:23:30.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know that very well, Mr. Jamling.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.80,0:23:34.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to use my services,\NI'll gladly start as soon tomorrow morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.24,0:23:36.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, even starting tonight is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.79,0:23:39.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jamling...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.60,0:24:07.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A child who suddenly fell sick\Nis brought to Dr. Deighton's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.49,0:24:11.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But because Doctor is so drunk,\Nhe can't even walk straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.29,0:24:15.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"The Boozed Doctor".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.09,0:24:16.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
